 we watch and listen through gritted teeth, Dislike-Minded listens to what is being said, and presents a bold case for a new line of audience research within communication, media, and cultural studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAesthetics. 0aLikes and dislikes. 0aMass mediaxAudiences. 0aSocial media. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aPierre Bourdieu.  aaudiences.  afailure.  afans.  ataste.  atelevision.40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479810000.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479810000423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479810000/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles